    "path": "src/agent/session",
    "name": "session",
    "purpose": "Owns the agent session runtime. session.rs defines Session, whose new builds the SessionContext and immediately spawns the client and host channel workers (there is no separate run); it drives synchronous task creation (locking the shared client/host senders through std::sync::Mutex, reporting CreateFailed via try_send, and creating each Task through Task::new, which now starts its own worker) and SessionEvent routing; its client/host recv loops still run inside per-connection current-thread tokio runtimes to await remoc recv. session_context.rs defines SessionContext, which owns the TaskId-keyed task WorkQueue and the shared client/host remoc mpsc endpoints, all initialized behind std::sync::Mutex. mod.rs is namespace and re-export wiring only.",
    "changeStatus": "modified"
  },
